  "prompt": "What is SIN time?",
  "response": "SIN time refers to the time zone for Singapore, which is typically identified by the abbreviation SIN. Singapore operates on Singapore Standard Time (SGT), which is UTC+8 hours. Therefore, SIN time is 8 hours ahead of Coordinated Universal Time (UTC+8). Singapore does not observe daylight saving time, so this time offset remains constant throughout the year.",
